The paper deals with the design of transceivers for the multiple-input-multiple-output (MIMO) interference channel, which is a topic in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a method for optimizing the precoders and equalizers to mitigate interference, which is a problem in control systems (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of scalar feedback signals to regulate transmission power, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
